flowRoot.flowPara: Tools for Adaptation - Integrating Environment, Genotype and Phenotype
Kevin Murray1, Tim Brown1, Riyan Cheng1, Steve Eichten1, Xavier Sirault2, Norman Warthmann1, Justin Borevitz1
What is it?
- Integrated plant growth facility, sample tracking, genomics, phenomics and statistical analysis
- Open-source computational pipelines for cross-scale genome analysis and image analysis for automated phenotyping
- >30k lines of code, >15 software projects, > 1500 git commit
- Project outline published in Current Opinions[1]
The SpectralPhenoClimatron
- Controlled environment plant growth facility fitted with Mulitspectral LED lamps
- DSLR cameras, <1min resolution in daylight, ~300x300px/plant
- SolarCalc[α] simulates regional climates without weather[2]
- SPCControl[β] controls multispectral lamps, temperature, humidty and cameras
i tim
Automated, Real-time Phenomics
- EyePi[δ]: Raspberry Pi-based image aquisition hardware & software
- Timestreamlib[ε]: time series image format and manipulation library
- Image analysis for correction, segmentation, derandomisation
- Automated batch image analysis
- GUI for interactive analysis
- Python 2.7 & 3.3+, cross platform, Open Source (GPL licensed)
TV GOES HERE
Cross-scale Genomics
- Reduced representation sequencing method
- Custom optimised libary preparation protocol; 576-1152 samples per lane
- Custom variant calling pipeline build on TASSEL[3]
Low-coverage Whole-genome Sequencing
- Low-cost library preparation protocol [4]
- Advanced robotics providing tissue grinding, liquid handling, SPRI.
- Novel alignment-free variant calling algorithms (in initial development)
Advanced Statistical Association Analysis
- QTLRel[η]: Statistical methods to map QTLs in structured populations [7]
- QTL/GWA analysis with increased statsistical power by combining traits in join analysis [C]
- Real-time QTL mapping, allowing interactive adjustment of experiemntal conditions
Future Projects
- Functional Structural Plant Models: Allow statisical prediction of phenotypes from genetics and envrionment
- Expanding into non-model crop/crop wild relative species
